---
description: Runtime parity and user-facing simulator surface rules
globs:
  - src/pvtapp/**/*.py
  - src/pvtcore/**/*.py
  - tests/**/*.py
  - README.md
  - docs/runtime_surface_standard.md
---

- Enforce `docs/runtime_surface_standard.md`. Domain-level features in `pvtcore` must be runtime-wired, explicitly marked experimental/not app-supported, or removed.
- GUI controls and runtime config must drive the actual calculation path. Display-only controls that imply runtime behavior are not acceptable.
- Preserve method context and artifact provenance through the run: EOS, characterization, BIP handling, lumping/delumping, and reported basis should stay auditable.
- `src/pvtapp/capabilities.py`, `src/pvtapp/schemas.py`, and `src/pvtapp/job_runner.py` are the main runtime choke points for supported workflows.
- If runtime support changes, update `README.md` and the relevant `docs/` files in the same slice.